str2: A woman, wife, my lady. Probably from the base of ginomai; a woman; specially, a wife.

parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: See! Lo! Behold! Look! Second person singular imperative middle voice of eido; used as imperative lo!

str2: To have, hold, possess. Including an alternate form scheo skheh'-o; a primary verb; to hold.
From asthenes; feebleness; by implication, malady; morally, frailty.
A year. Apparently a primary word; a year.

parse: Verb - Imperfect Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: To be bowed together, bent double. From sun and kupto; to stoop altogether, i.e. Be completely overcome by.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Middle or Passive - Nominative Feminine Singular
str2: (a) I am powerful, have (the) power, (b) I am able, I can. Of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.
To raise myself, look up, be elated. From ana and kupto; to unbend, i.e. Rise; figuratively, be elated.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
